
For each point @"A"@ determine the quadrant to which it belongs and the coordinates 
@center@ of the point @"M"@ symmetric with respect to the @"x"@ axis, 
@center@ of the point @"N"@ symmetric with respect to the @"y"@ axis,
to the point @"A"@.
@repeat(3)@ 
@vspace@
@center@ @"A"@ = (@xa@, @ya@) @hspacept(15)@ kvadrant @hspacept(3)@ @lib.check_one_option_dropdown(posit, posit[ind])@
@center@ @"M"@ = (@lib.check_number(xm,25)@, @lib.check_number(ym,15)@), @hspacept(5)@ @"N"@ = (@lib.check_number(xn,25)@, @lib.check_number(yn,15)@) 
@/repeat@  